    "what_description": "Plantago lanceolata is a perennial herbaceous plant that belongs to the family Plantaginaceae. It grows 10-60 cm tall, with a lance-shaped leaf that is 5-15 cm long and 1-3 cm wide, and a leaf shape that tapers to a narrow tip. The plant produces a spike-like inflorescence, 2-5 cm long, containing small white flowers that are 3-4 mm in diameter. Each flower has 5 stamens and 1 pistil, with a 5-lobed calyx and a 5-lobed corolla. The plant has a fibrous rhizome and produces small, 4-6 mm long, brownish-grey seeds with a fine reticulate pattern.",
