    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Plantago lanceolata are its anti-inflammatory effects, which are attributed to the presence of flavonoids, that help reduce swelling and alleviate pain in conditions such as arthritis. Plantago lanceolata also exhibits antimicrobial properties due to the action of saponins, which inhibit the growth of microorganisms and prevent infections. The antioxidant properties of this plant are a result of the activity of volatile oils, which neutralize free radicals and protect against oxidative stress. Furthermore, it has expectorant properties, which are beneficial in respiratory disorders such as bronchitis, as the bioactive compounds stimulate the production of mucus and facilitate its expulsion. Additionally, the analgesic properties of Plantago lanceolata are due to the action of sesquiterpenes, which reduce pain and discomfort in various conditions.",
