    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effect of using Plantago lanceolata are numerous and can be severe if not used properly, as it may interact with medications such as blood thinners, diabetes medications, and blood pressure medications, which can lead to adverse effects, including excessive bleeding and low blood sugar. Individuals may experience allergic reactions, including hives, itching, and difficulty breathing, due to the plant's high content of allergenic compounds like sesquiterpene lactones. Furthermore, Plantago lanceolata may also induce allergic reactions in some people, exacerbating existing allergies, particularly those related to ragweed and other plants in the same family. Additionally, consuming large quantities of the plant may induce diarrhea due to its high content of fiber and other compounds that can disrupt digestive system. It is essential to consult a healthcare professional before using Plantago lanceolata to avoid these potential side effects."
